The paper deals with hierarchical clustering, which is a common topic in machine learning and data analysis. The use of prior information and structural constraints is also a popular area of research in these fields. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions optimization and regularization techniques, which are common in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) subfields. Finally, the paper applies the approach to a real dataset for taxonomy, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or other subfields related to image or data analysis.
